{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>This entry represents pleiotropic repressors in Bacillus subtilis, CodY, and other Firmicutes (low-GC Gram-positive bacteria) that respond to intracellular levels of GTP and branched chain amino acids. CodY is a DNA-binding protein that represses the expression of many genes that are induced as cells make the transition from rapid exponential growth to stationary phase and sporulation. It is a GTP-binding protein that senses the intracellular GTP concentration as an indicator of nutritional limitations. At low GTP concentration it no longer binds GTP and stops to act as a transcriptional repressor [[cite:PUB00054248], [cite:PUB00054249]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure {"accession" "2b18", "name" "N-terminal GAF domain of transcriptional pleiotropic repressor CodY."}, :overlaps-with [{"accession" "IPR029016", "name" "GAF-like domain superfamily", "type" "homologous_superfamily"}], :member-databases {"panther" {"PTHR40062" "GTP-SENSING TRANSCRIPTIONAL PLEIOTROPIC REPRESSOR CODY"}, "hamap" {"MF_00621" "Global transcriptional regulator CodY [codY]"}, "pirsf" {"PIRSF011572" "GTP-sensing transcription pleiotropic repressor CodY"}, "ncbifam" {"TIGR02787" "GTP-sensing pleiotropic transcriptional regulator CodY"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Global transcriptional regulator CodY", "short" "CodY"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 16, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 1259, "taxa" 4327, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 4177, "sets" 0, "proteins" 4176, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 3271}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR014154", :literature {"PUB00054248" {"URL" nil, "issue" "20", "authors" ["Serror P" "Sonenshein AL."], "ISO_journal" "J. Bacteriol.", "DOI_URL" nil, "medline_journal" "J Bacteriol", "title" "CodY is required for nutrit